title: Astra launch of NASA TROPICS cubesats fails
summary: An Astra launch of two NASA cubesats to monitor tropical storms failed June 12 when the rocket’s upper stage shut down prematurely.

title: Astra launch fails on first TROPICS flight for NASA
summary: The first of three flights to launch the TROPICS satellites for NASA lifted off on Sunday during at 1:43 PM EDT (17:43 UTC). Astra’s LV0010 vehicle launched from SLC-46 at the Cape Canaveral Space Force Station, making the company’s seventh orbital launch attempt.

title: DoD space agency to acquire 10 satellites for experiments in low Earth orbit
summary: The Space Development Agency is looking to acquire as many as 10 satellites to host military payloads for experiments in low Earth orbit.

title: Europa Clipper’s main body complete, teams continue work toward 2024 launch
summary: In early June, the main body of NASA’s upcoming Europa Clipper spacecraft completed construction and was shipped to NASA’s Jet Propulsion Laboratory (JPL) in Pasadena, California soon after. The arrival of Europa Clipper’s main body marks a major milestone in the construction of the spacecraft and shows that the spacecraft and its teams are on track for a launch in 2024.

title: U.S. Space Force orders eight launches from ULA and SpaceX
summary: The U.S. Space Force recently ordered five military satellite launches from United Launch Alliance and three from SpaceX, awards valued at $846 million for missions scheduled to fly in the next two years.
